# Cursor AI Rules — Next.js SST Boilerplate
# These rules are also compatible with other AI coding assistants.

## Tech Stack
- Next.js 16 (App Router, TypeScript, SSR via SST/OpenNext)
- Vanilla CSS with custom properties (NO Tailwind)
- AWS CloudFront + Lambda + S3 via SST v4 Ion
- Direct CLI deployment (`npx sst deploy`)

## Coding Standards
- TypeScript strict mode, no `any`
- Named exports for components
- Path aliases: `@/*` → `./src/*`
- BEM naming for CSS: `.block__element--modifier`
- CSS tokens via `var(--custom-property)`
- Server Components by default

## File Conventions
- Components: `src/components/PascalCase.tsx`
- Pages: `src/app/**/page.tsx`
- Styles: `src/app/globals.css` (design system)
- Infrastructure: `sst.config.ts`

## Versioning
- Follow SemVer (MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH)
- Update CHANGELOG.md on every commit (Keep a Changelog format)
- Bump version in package.json when releasing

## Important
- This is a FULL-STACK SSR app — API routes, Server Actions, ISR supported
- Images are optimized by Next.js on the server (Lambda)
- Deploy via `npx sst deploy --stage production`
